>Description:
http://docs.racket-lang.org/redex/tutorial.html

"Most of the rules use use types, or give base types to atomic expressions, but the fourth rule is worth a special look. It says that if a variable typechecks in some environment, then it also type checks in an extended environment, provided that the environment extension does not use the variable in question."

I think it should be the *fifth* rule.
